Thilo Sarrazin, the former
Bundesbank board member who quit last year after comments on
Jews and Muslims sparked political outrage, can remain a member
of the  Social Democratic Party , Deutsche Presse Agentur said.  The SPD decided late yesterday not to exclude Sarrazin, DPA
reported today, without saying where it got the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
